          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Assad leaves, and Syrians return</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The fall of Bashar al-Assad’s regime marks a crucial shift in the <a href="https://www.britannica.com/event/Syrian-Civil-War" target="_blank">Syrian Civil War</a>, with rebel forces like Hayat Tahrir al-Sham gaining ground and forcing Assad to <a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/syria-bashar-assad-russia-rebels-ryabkov-sanctuary-rcna183594" target="_blank">flee to Russia</a> after 24 years in power. Since 2011, the conflict has caused immense suffering, with hundreds of thousands dead and millions displaced. While some refugees are <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20241210-the-road-to-damascus-syrian-exiles-return-home-to-celebrate-fall-of-assad" target="_blank">returning</a> home, many remain at the Turkish border, <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cvg6eeg87lqo" target="_blank">uncertain</a> about safety in Syria. Experts caution that rebuilding will take time due to damaged infrastructure and a lack of essential services, leaving Syrian refugees in countries like Germany grappling <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2024/dec/11/syrians-living-in-berlin-debate-return" target="_blank">with the choice</a> between safety and an uncertain future.</p>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
