          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Last term for Bernie Sanders</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Bernie Sanders, the independent senator from Vermont, <a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2024/12/10/bernie-sanders-senate-term-00193608" target="_blank">believes</a> his upcoming fourth term, starting in January 2025, will probably be his last at age 83. Bernie Sanders has served in Congress since 1991, significantly influencing the progressive movement, including running for president twice in 2016 and 2020. Sanders has been <a href="https://www.politico.com/live-updates/2024/11/06/2024-election-results-live-coverage-updates-analysis/bernie-sanders-election-response-00187980" target="_blank">critical</a> of the Democratic Party for failing to address the concerns of working-class Americans and believes Democrats are out of touch with average citizens. While he supports some of President Biden’s initiatives, he urges the party to adopt more progressive ideals to stay relevant. Sanders will lose his position at the Health, Education, Labor, and Pension Committee in January, but he hopes to return if Democrats win the Senate.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
