        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Hannah Kobayashi, the Hawaiian woman who went missing in Los Angeles, has been <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/11/us/hannah-kobayashi-found-update-father/index.html" target="_blank">found safe</a>, her family announced. She gained attention after <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/11/26/us/hannah-kobayashi-missing-woman-what-we-know/index.html" target="_blank">missing</a> her connecting flight to New York and was seen on surveillance footage with an unidentified man before her case was reclassified as a voluntary disappearance. Tragically, her father, <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/ckgvxyrj8k5o" target="_blank">Ryan Kobayashi</a>, who came to help in the search, was found dead from suicide. Hannah traveled to Mexico after purchasing a ticket and communicated concerns about her safety before ceasing contact. While her family is deeply affected, they expressed relief at her safe return and requested privacy.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
