              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">Who exactly is Luigi Mangione?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The case of Luigi Mangione, accused of murdering UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson, highlights a troubling blend of personal anguish and systemic issues. The 26-year-old Ivy League graduate <a href="https://m.economictimes.com/news/international/global-trends/no-physical-intimacy-how-chronic-back-pain-allegedly-pushed-luigi-mangione-to-kill-unitedhealthcare-ceo/amp_articleshow/116199265.cms" target="_blank">struggled</a> with chronic back pain and underwent spinal fusion surgery, leaving him physically and emotionally exhausted. This situation reportedly isolated him and fueled his discontent with the healthcare system.</p>
        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Despite his extremely <a href="https://www.newsweek.com/luigi-mangione-louis-father-wealthy-1999684" target="_blank">privileged</a> upbringing, he grew distant from his family. His alleged crime opened conversations across the political spectrum about insurance companies' unorthodox tactics and the shortcomings of the American healthcare system. While framed as “anti-capitalist,” Mangione’s social media interactions show a mix of admiration for figures like <a href="https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/crime/luigi-mangione-murder-unitedhealthcare-elon-musk-b2661922.html" target="_blank">Elon Musk</a> and criticisms of modern societal norms. His story blends many elements of healthcare, mental health, and extremism.</p>
       <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">At his arrest, Mangione carried a <a href="https://www.btimesonline.com/articles/171506/20241210/unitedhealthcare-ceo-s-alleged-killer-luigi-mangione-left-manifesto-condemning-corporate-greed-in-health-industry.htm" target="_blank">manifesto</a> denouncing corporate greed and healthcare's profit-driven approach. His writings reveal a heavy disenfranchisement with his health challenges and systemic failures. However, the case with Luigi Mangione does more than just open these conversations. It exposes America’s <a href="https://english.elpais.com/usa/2024-12-12/in-love-with-a-killer-how-the-internet-became-obsessed-with-luigi-mangione.html" target="_blank">obsession</a> with hero worship and vigilante justice, and the public quickly worshipped him on both sides of the political aisle. His arrest broke the internet, and he was painted as some Robin Hood character.</p>
        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">This is not a new phenomenon. However, in what people imagine in civilized democracies, vigilante justice and gunning someone down isn’t part of it. There should be more constructive ways to enact change.</p>
      
        </mj-text>
    </mj-column>
